Text.Value: You rejected me before - I'm in no mood for dispensing favours.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This QN if the player was previously refused entry by the cellar master.

Text.Value: Of course... please, forget I said anything. Praise the Absolute.
Even if someone managed to get that far, they'd already be as good as dead.
These were gifts from the Absolute, for my loyalty. I used them to take the head of the Lolth priestess who cut off my hands.

EditorData.NodeContext: A touch defensive. He's proud, but old wounds remain

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: A male drow paces back and forth, practicing strikes and slashes at thin air with a pair of cruel-looking short swords. On closer inspection, it seems that they’re actually grafted onto the stumps of his forearms. He performs a quick flurry of strikes at an imaginary enemy.

Text.Value: I was told you've been granted passage to the Illumination Chamber.
Leave.
Nice blades. Don't think I'd trade my hands for them, though.
You honour me. I will not let you down.
Whoever your mistress is, she needs to rein in that tongue of yours. Or remove it.
Warriors, nobility, power brokers... important people. Those the Absolute has use for.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He studies the player critically, then shoos them away with a bladed arm.

Text.Value: Chosen Ketheric is the judge. I am the executioner - if you press me.
Provoking me is a most painful means of suicide. Leave, or I'll fill this chamber with your screams.
We all serve the Absolute here, remember? I don't have to answer to the likes of you ever again.
Leave without dignifying him with an answer.
You are not among them. Leave.
No one can make it past these doors - past me - without Illumination.
Please, enter. The defences will not harm one of the Illuminated - Chosen Ketheric would see me burn if anything befell you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He gestures to the double doors.
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: specifics of the actual trap avoidance/disarm clue TBD.

Text.Value: Attack.
You will not pass me. Leave.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This node only if the cellar master didn't reiterate he isn't letting the player pass yet

Text.Value: Please, the Path of Illumination is open to you. Praise the Absolute.
I still have her head in my chamber. Part of my collection.
I see what you're doing - trying to trick me into talking, saying more than I should. It won't work.
You're no judge of me.
Curious. I thought male drow were nothing but cup-bearers and foot-stools.
Perhaps you can put in a word for me - I am loyal. I am ready. Someone like you could help Chosen Ketheric see the true extent of my service towards him.
If you were truly ready, you'd have been summoned.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This QN if the player was NOT previously refused entry by the cellar master.

Text.Value: If you are found worthy of Illumination, I will know. Until then, these doors are closed to you.
There has to be another way through - there's always another way.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Active roll available after the cellar master has reiterated the player cannot pass ( local flag SeekingEntry set)

Text.Value: Stand aside. I am a True Soul.
I'll see what I can do.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He spots the player. The grin fades. He lowers his blades and bows slightly.

Text.Value: I answer to Chosen Ketheric, and he speaks for the Absolute. Z'rell has no power down here.
Beyond those doors, one wrong step will kill you. Only those without a trace of fear could possibly survive.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Quest flag needed - clue about how the death trap works

Text.Value: I... of course. Please, enter. Praise the Absolute.
That's not enough - not for here. None pass me without Chosen Ketheric's favour.

EditorData.NodeContext: Unimpressed by the player's attempt to pull rank.

Text.Value: Fair enough. I'll just kill you.
Stop. None but those destined for Illumination are allowed to pass me, with Chosen Ketheric's blessing.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The drow spots the player and scowls.

Text.Value: Do you think Disciple Z'rell would agree with you?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Global knows Z'rell flag first sets during the ground floor execution scene.

Text.Value: I serve no one but the Absolute. He trusts me. He honours me.

Synopsis: Next to the jail, there is an imposing door guarded by the cellar master, who has short swords grafted onto the stumps of his forearms. We can pass him if Ketheric sent us here, or if we succeed a hard persuasion.
